SOP: Conveyor Belt Mistracking and Drive Vibration

1. Stop material feed and clear loaded belt where safe.
2. Lock out conveyor drive, gearbox, and take-up energy sources.
3. Inspect belt edge, pulley lagging, idlers, skirt boards, and take-up tension.
4. Align return idlers and verify pulley crown and lagging condition.
5. Inspect drive-end bearings and coupling if vibration is above warning threshold.
6. Run unloaded belt, then loaded belt, and record tracking and motor current.
